race.comment: CHARINO (3) showed a lot of tenacity when overcoming a wide gate to score by more than a length in a good field at Ascot 15 days ago, and he will have a better draw this time. This is not much harder, and with a kg less to carry, he can repeat the dose. SUPERNATURAL (9) charged home too late when finishing runner-up by a nose at Ascot last time out, and she will drop 3.5kg from that run. William Pike sticks with her, and so do we. ZING TO WIN (5) is resuming from a 7-week freshen up to have his first run on this track. He scored a brace at Geraldton during the spring and is worth including in all combinations here. CRIPPALENKO (2) has not fired this prep, but will have a better draw this time compared to his last 3 starts. His best is good enough to see him figure in the finish here. WILD IMAGINATION (1) will be chasing a hat-trick of wins after a recent double at Esperance. She has won 14 races all told, and that makes her worthy of respect, even in this tough field.
